<subSubSection id="71A76560D054FFE9C18AFB90FA5562D4" pageId="6" pageNumber="215" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="390236EBD054FFE9C18AFB90FA5562D4" blockId="6.[136,1452,1094,1231]" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">
Widely distributed in cold environments, chiefly in the Southern Hemisphere but also with isolated occurrences in northern polar regions. It is the commonest species of the genus in 
<collectingRegion id="FB79F809D054FFE9C284FBBCFC2D629D" box="[902,1009,1130,1156]" country="Australia" name="Tasmania" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">Tasmania</collectingRegion>
where it occurs on most rock 
<typeStatus id="E6068849D054FFE9C44EFBBDFA5B629C" box="[1356,1415,1131,1157]" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">types</typeStatus>
on high mountains as well as on lower pinnacles. Descriptive data are provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="5D2C4B1AD054FFE9C515FB58FB0C62B1" author="Rambold, G." box="[1047,1232,1166,1192]" pageId="6" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 345" refId="ref8144" refString="Rambold, G. (1989) A monograph of the saxicolous lecideoid lichens of Australia (excl. Tasmania). Bibliotheca Lichenologica 34: 1 - 345." type="journal article" year="1989">Rambold (1989)</bibRefCitation>
<bibRefCitation id="5D2C4B1AD054FFE9C5DAFB58FF0962D5" author="Hertel, H. &amp; Rambold, G." pageId="6" pageNumber="215" pagination="145 - 189" refId="ref7543" refString="Hertel, H. &amp; Rambold, G. (1990) Zur Kenntnis der Familie Rimulariaceae (Lecanorales). Bibliotheca Lichenologica 38: 145 - 189." type="journal article" year="1990">Hertel &amp; Rambold (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5D2C4B1AD054FFE9C1E3FB62FE0962D5" author="Ovstedal, D. O. &amp; Tonsberg, T. &amp; Elvebakk, A." box="[225,469,1202,1231]" pageId="6" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 393" refId="ref8095" refString="Ovstedal, D. O., Tonsberg, T. &amp; Elvebakk, A. (2009) The lichen flora of Svalbard. Sommerfeltia 33: 1 - 393. https: // doi. org / 10.2478 / v 10208 - 011 - 0013 - 5" type="journal article" year="2009">
Øvstedal 
<emphasis id="0BC9EAF9D054FFE9C049FB65FE5862D5" box="[331,388,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
and, for Tasmanian material, 
<bibRefCitation id="5D2C4B1AD054FFE9C221FB64FC3F62D5" author="Kantvilas, G." box="[803,995,1202,1228]" pageId="6" pageNumber="215" pagination="349 - 364" refId="ref7624" refString="Kantvilas, G. (2014) New species of the genus Rimularia Nyl. from Tasmania. Lichenologist 46: 349 - 364. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0024282913000595" type="journal article" year="2014">Kantvilas (2014)</bibRefCitation>
. This is the 
<typeStatus id="E6068849D054FFE9C56BFB65FB4562D4" box="[1129,1177,1203,1229]" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus.
</paragraph>
